<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/98844519-william-stclaire"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_100x100-c7bfe730633c9983e27caaa66a8e244a.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/98844519-william-stclaire">William Stclaire</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Can&apos;t really think of any right off hand, but I have read many articles that claim Saunnier was stealing money from the good people who paid him to do<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Can't really think of any right off hand, but I have read many articles that claim Saunnier was stealing money from the good people who paid him to do religious mass among other stuff. But I do also like to think of him as an enigma and love the mystery surrounding the place, dare I say ,"mystery" or should it be "history", anyway, I'm way too sentimental for my own good and I was enthralled by this book.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
