<span id="freeTextContainer12467018189161528548">I originally approached the book with the idea that even if the &quot;history&quot; was wonky, it will be entertaining to read. I was sorely disappointed. It was uphill all the way, especially in the middle, when you get bogged down in all those dynasties.<br/><br/>However, I&apos;m giving it two stars for the chapters towards the end. The speculations in there have given the myth-lover in me have one more go at the Bible, and the enigmatic figure of the Christ.<br/><br/>Overall opinion? A boring book with some entertaining specu</span>
  <span id="freeText12467018189161528548" style="display:none">I originally approached the book with the idea that even if the "history" was wonky, it will be entertaining to read. I was sorely disappointed. It was uphill all the way, especially in the middle, when you get bogged down in all those dynasties.<br /><br />However, I'm giving it two stars for the chapters towards the end. The speculations in there have given the myth-lover in me have one more go at the Bible, and the enigmatic figure of the Christ.<br /><br />Overall opinion? A boring book with some entertaining speculations.</span>
